<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="SC3" checkit-title="Venn Diagrams">
    <statement>
        <p>
            A survey asks 400 people the following question: "Do you prefer shopping online or shopping in a store?" In their answer, the respondents can specify one of the two options, both, or neither. Suppose 37 reported that they prefer shopping in a store only, 99 reported that they prefer shopping in a store, 139 reported that they prefer shopping online, and 77 reported that they prefer shopping online only.
            <ol>
                <li>Draw a Venn diagram of the situation. Use the information in the problem to clearly label the diagram.</li>
                <li>How many people  reported that they prefer neither shopping online nor shopping in a store?</li>
                <li>How many people  reported that they prefer both shopping online and shopping in a store?</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>In general you should draw overlapping circles contained in a larger rectangle. From the information given in this problem, 400 is the amount for the entire rectangle, 37 is the number for the crescent moon part of shopping in a store, 99 is the number for the entire shopping in a store circle, 139 is the number for the entire shopping online circle, and 77 is the number for the crescent moon part of shopping online.</li>
                <li>224 reported that they prefer neither shopping online nor shopping in a store.</li>
                <li>62 reported that they prefer both shopping online and shopping in a store.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
